If your school uses Wilma, you can import students by copy-pasting the student list from Wilma. The required format for the input is as follows: < class > < last name > < first name > For example: 9b Duck Donald9b Duck Daisy9c Duck Scrooge Students are separated by line-breaks so that one line of text represents one student. Each piece of information (class, last name, first name) is separated by a single space. You can obtain the student list from Wilma by selecting "Print course book" and selecting the students in the table.
Enter student information in the format <class> <last name> <first name>, one student per line.
